data.enText: to remove liquid from a surface by pressing soft paper or cloth on it
to make a spot or spots of ink fall on paper
blot your copybook

data.chText: 做出有损形象的事；玷污名誉
data.enText: to do sth to spoil the opinion that other people have of you
blot sth↔out
to cover or hide sth completely
Clouds blotted out the sun.

data.chText: 有意地忘记（不愉快的记忆或想法）；抹去
data.enText: to deliberately try to forget an unpleasant memory or thought

data.chText: 他尽量不去想海伦的那张忧伤的脸。
data.enText: He tried to blot out the image of Helen's sad face.
a spot or dirty mark on sth, made by ink, etc.

data.chText: 有损形象（或幸福）的事情；污点
data.enText: something that spoils the opinion that other people have of you, or your happiness

data.chText: 她卷入了这次欺诈案，在她的品格上留下了一个很大的污点。
data.enText: Her involvement in the fraud has left a serious blot on her character.

data.text: mark ♦ stain ♦ streak ♦ speck ♦ blot ♦ smear ♦ spot

data.chText: 以上各词均指污点、斑点、污迹。
data.enText: These are all words for a small area of dirt or another substance on a surface.
mark
a small area of dirt or other substance on the surface of sth, especially one that spoils its appearance

data.chText: 孩子们把厨房的地板弄得污迹斑斑。
data.enText: The kids left dirty marks all over the kitchen floor.
stain
a dirty mark on sth that is difficult to remove, especially one made by a liquid
blood stains
streak
a long thin mark or line that is a different colour from the surface it is on
She had streaks of grey in her hair.
speck
a very small mark, spot or piece of a substance on sth
There isn't a speck of dust anywhere in the house.
blot
a spot or dirty mark left on sth by a substance such as ink or paint being dropped on a surface
smear
a mark made by sth such as oil or paint being spread or rubbed on a surface
spot
a small dirty mark on sth
There were grease spots all over the walls.
a streak/speck/blot/smear/spot of sth
a dirty mark/stain/streak/speck/smear/spot
an ink mark/stain/blot/spot
a(n) oil/grease/paint mark/stain/spot
to leave a mark/stain/streak/speck/blot/smear/spot
to get a mark/stain/spot out of sth

trans: 抹去（记忆）；排除，挤掉（其他想法或记忆）

tr: an act that brings discredit to the person who does it
example: he made a huge blot on his copybook
he had a smudge on his cheek

tr: make a spot or mark onto

value.def: If something is a blot on a person's or thing's reputation, it spoils their reputation.

example.ex: ...a blot on the reputation of the architectural profession...
example.tran: 败坏建筑业名声的污点

example.ex: This drugs scandal is another blot on the Olympics.
example.tran: 这次的兴奋剂丑闻又给奥林匹克运动会抹了黑。

value.def: A blot is a drop of liquid that has fallen on to a surface and has dried.
If you blot a surface, you remove liquid from it by pressing a piece of soft paper or cloth onto it.

example.ex: Before applying make-up, blot the face with a tissue to remove any excess oils...
example.tran: 上妆前，先用面巾纸把脸上多余的油吸干。

value.def: If you describe something such as a building as a blot on the landscape, you mean that you think it is very ugly and spoils an otherwise attractive place.

example.ex: The developers insist the 80m village will not leave a blot on the landscape.
example.tran: 开发商们坚称这个耗资8,000万的居住区不会破坏风景。

value.tran: 破坏整体美的事物；煞风景的事物

trans: 排除，挤掉（其他想法或记忆）
